description:
Malaysian authorities have ramped up security across Kuala Lumpur ahead of the ASEAN Summit 2025, as the city prepares to host leaders from the 10-member bloc and dialogue partners including the United States, China, Japan, India, and Australia.
The summit comes at a sensitive time for the region, with ongoing South China Sea tensions, the crisis in Myanmar, and efforts to strengthen economic integration amid global trade uncertainties.
Officials have implemented tight security measures, including thorough entry checks and police cordons around the Kuala Lumpur Convention Centre, ensuring the summit proceeds smoothly and safely.
Over the next three days, leaders will discuss maritime disputes, regional security, and economic resilience, navigating both geopolitical challenges and the influence of major global powers.
